column2:
grouped_byDay <- dplyr::tbl(dbconn,
                            "fltrd_data") |>
    dplyr::select(started_at,
                  member_casual) |>
    dplyr::collect() |>
    dplyr::mutate(started_at = as.Date(started_at)) |>
    dplyr::group_by(started_at,
                    member_casual) |>
    dplyr::summarize(n = dplyr::n(),
                     sdev = stats::sd(n))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'started_at'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
